Program: The History Hour
Title: China's breakthrough malaria cure
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqmz
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 19 Mar 2019
How an ancient Chinese remedy provided a 1970s breakthrough in the fight against malaria; the bombing of Dresden in the Second World War that inspired Kurt Vonnegut's anti-war novel Slaughterhouse Five; the fall of Singapore; plus the town that America built in Afghanistan's south-western desert, and 'was Lenin a mushroom' - a satirical re-writing of Soviet history. Photo: Professor Lang Linfu (Family archives) Show less